<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-09T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-09T01:00:00-05:00" n="427" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">824.796/207: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-09T01:00:00-05:00">December 9, 1941—1
                                a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>252. Your 346, November 29, and despatch 1167, October 8.<note n="31" xml:id="d427fn1">Latter not printed.</note> Department, Panagra and
                            the Defense Supplies Corporation have no <pb facs="0422" n="412" xml:id="pg_412"/> objection to the transfer of control of civil and
                            commercial aviation from the Ministry of Communications to the Ministry
                            of Defense, provided it is clearly understood with the Foreign Office
                            that the obligation entered into by the Ministry of Communications with
                            the Defense Supplies Corporation will be assumed by the Ministry of
                            Defense.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>